
<sellerabr>RANK XEROX</sellerabr> {<sellercode>XRX</sellercode>} TO SELL SOUTH AFRICAN UNIT
    NEW YORK, March 19 - Xerox Corp's U.K. unit, <seller>Rank Xerox
Ltd</seller>, said it <status>agreed in principle</status> to sell its <acqloc>South African</acqloc>
company, <acquired>Rank Xerox South Africa Pty Ltd</acquired>, to {<purchaser>Altron Group</purchaser>'s}
Fintech unit.
    Terms of the deal were not disclosed.
    <purchabr>Altron</purchabr> said the acquisition was key to making Fintech an
office systems company.
    The <acqabr>South African Rank Xerox</acqabr> unit sells <acqbus>copiers and
duplicators</acqbus> throughout <acqloc>South Africa</acqloc> and in Namibia (South West
Africa). It has over 800 employees, all of whom will be
retained by Fintech when the deal closes, <sellerabr>Rank Xerox</sellerabr> said.
